<div id="review_2314388790" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2314388790" />
    <a title="Jeremy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9988962-jeremy"><img alt="Jeremy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486326794p2/9988962.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2314388790?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeremy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeremy" href="/user/show/9988962-jeremy">Jeremy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2314388790" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3057316433693455342">Drunken, lurid, and hilarious shenanigans as only the aging Bukowski could tell. He also branches out from the seemingly autobiographical fare to curveball surreal pieces with real power and literature rants that show Bukowski knew better than the critics of his time. Will Patton in the audiobook delivers an all-time awesome performance that was recognized by the Audies.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

